cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.IR 

The paper discusses a method for learning graph embeddings, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The approach also involves taking pairwise node similarities into account, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper evaluates the method on semantic similarity and word sense disambiguation tasks, which are also common in computational linguistics (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
